Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve @grape tomatoes{4} lengthwise.

== Ginger Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, half the scallion whites, and @ginger{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-3%minutes}.

Stir in 1¼ cups water and @pho stock concentrate{1}; bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Sesame Chili Beef ==

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}, @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon}, and half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}.

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add beef to bowl with sesame-chili mixture; press to coat all sides.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add beef and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-7%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer beef to a #plate{} (it'll finish cooking in the next step). Wipe out pan.

== Garlic Broccoli ==

While beef cooks, toss broccoli on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes}.

Once broccoli has roasted for ~{5%minutes}, remove sheet from oven. Carefully place beef on empty side of sheet. Return to top rack and roast until broccoli is browned and tender and beef reaches desired doneness, ~{8-10%minutes} more.

== Soy Butter Tomatoes ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Add tomatoes and remaining scallion whites; cook until tomatoes begin to burst, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, ¼ cup water, and @sugar{1%teaspoon}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture is slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%TBSP} until melted.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in scallion greens and @butter{1%TBSP} until melted and combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Slice beef against the grain.

Divide rice between plates. Top with broccoli and beef in separate sections; spoon as many tomatoes as you like over beef. Serve with any remaining tomatoes on the side.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.